# Agent Team and Patterns

Cursor has no Claude Agent Teams runtime. The "team" is a set of role
definitions plus an orchestrator that delegates via Cursor subagents (Task).

## Roles
- Orchestrator: plans, routes, and integrates. See `harness/agents/orchestrator.md`.
- Architect: design, SOLID/OCP, interfaces. See `harness/agents/architect.md`.
- Builder: implementation. See `harness/agents/builder.md`.
- Test Engineer: tests and coverage. See `harness/agents/test-engineer.md`.
- Reviewer: clean-code and quality review. See `harness/agents/reviewer.md`.
- Doc Writer: bilingual docs. See `harness/agents/doc-writer.md`.

## Architecture Patterns (mapped to Cursor)
- Pipeline: sequential dependent steps in one session.
- Fan-out/Fan-in: parallel independent subagents (Task), then merge.
- Expert Pool: select the role doc that fits the context.
- Producer-Reviewer: Builder produces, Reviewer subagent verifies.
- Supervisor: Orchestrator distributes tasks dynamically via Task.
- Hierarchical Delegation: subagents spawn sub-subagents (limited depth).

## How to Use
- Default to a single orchestrated session for small tasks.
- Use subagents (Task) for parallel research or independent build/review.
- Details and templates: `harness/patterns/architecture-patterns.md`.
